  <h4>Disabled state</h4>

  <p>In some cases, a form element can be disabled if a user needs to make an input somewhere else first. In this example, a user is <strong>required</strong> to select their department first and then optionally select their job role afterwards. A user can still submit a form successfully if they skip an optional form element.</p>

  <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    <!-- Temporary Warning alert until web component release -->
